CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 12, 1946, pg. 22, reads: "Local 609 Represented - At the Democratic Victory banquet in William Penn Hotel Monday night, Local 609, Garbage and Refuse Collectors, were represented by officers and members: Ollie Miller, trustee; John Wesley Turner, steward; Stedman Buckley, vice president; Haston Bolen, recording secretary; Theodore Johnson, secretary-treasurer and business agent; John S. Clark, steward; William Miller, president; William Finch, trustee; Clarence Fields, sergeant-at-arms, and Andrew Goodson, trustee. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of labor union members from Local 609 gathered around table 227, including Ollie Miller, John Wesley Turner, Stedman Buckley, Haston Bolen, Theodore Johnson, John S. Clark, William Miller, William Finch, Clarence Fields, and Andrew Goodson, in grand ballroom of William Penn Hotel for Democratic Victory banquet
